 the final chapter, on the Octavia attributed to Seneca and Juvenal's sixth Satire, broadens ideas of Hesiod's reception in Rome.  a1600aHesiodxCriticism and interpretation.00aHesiodxInfluence. 0aMythology, Greek, in literature. 0aMythology, Roman, in literature. 0aCambridge classical studies.423Publisher descriptionuhttp://catdir.loc.gov/catdir/enhancements/fy1501/2014021249-d.html413Table of contents onlyuhttp://catdir.loc.gov/catdir/enhancements/fy1501/2014021249-t.html423Contributor biographical informationuhttp://catdir.loc.gov/catdir/enhancements/fy1501/2014021249-b.html  aPA 4011 N66 2015c1hUAAU-Bi0162035237617  aPA 4011 N66 2015wLCc1i0162034578888d9/17/2015e9/16/2015lON_SHELFmUAAUGn2p$150.00rYsYtBOOKu2/11/201501ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n50062731bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/122220717